              <span class="sumTitle">üßº How to prepare</span>
              <span class="chip">pat dry harder</span>
              <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">‚ñæ</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="detailsBody">
              <ul>
                <li>Pat fillets <b>very dry</b>. This is half the game.</li>
                <li>Season both sides with salt/pepper; apply selected flavor path.</li>
                <li>Heat pan to medium; add oil until it shimmers.</li>
                <li>Cast iron = best crisp. Nonstick = easiest. Both work.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details style="margin-top:10px" open>
            <summary>
              <span class="sumTitle">üç≥ Cook steps</span>
              <span class="chip">one flip</span>
              <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">‚ñæ</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="detailsBody">
              <div class="steps">
                <div class="step"><p>Place <b>skin-side down</b>. Press gently for 10 seconds (prevents curling).</p></div>
                <div class="step"><p>Cook <b>3‚Äì5 min</b> skin-side down. Don‚Äôt move it early.</p></div>
                <div class="step"><p>Flip once. Cook <b>1‚Äì3 min</b> more to flake / 145¬∞F.</p></div>
                <div class="step"><p>Kill heat. Add butter + lemon; spoon over top.</p></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details style="margin-top:10px">
            <summary>
              <span class="sumTitle">üß© If it sticks‚Ä¶ (fast troubleshooting)</span>
              <span class="chip">decision tree</span>
              <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">‚ñæ</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="detailsBody">
              <ul>
                <li><b>Sticking immediately:</b> pan not hot enough OR fish too wet.</li>
                <li><b>Sticks when flipping:</b> you tried too early ‚Äî give it 30‚Äì60 seconds.</li>
                <li><b>Falling apart:</b> too many flips, or no skin, or it‚Äôs overcooked.</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="fine">Best fix: pat dry + wait for the release.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <div class="callout">
            <b>Tip:</b> If your fillet is thick (1¬Ω"), pan-sear then cover with a lid for 1‚Äì2 minutes to finish gently.
          </div>

          <p class="story fine" style="margin-top:10px">
            Pan trout is the ‚Äúspeedrun‚Äù method. Fast, crispy, and it makes you feel wildly competent.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- SIDES -->
      <section class="card method" id="sides" style="margin-top:14px" aria-label="Sides and timing plan">
        <div class="cardHeader">
          <div class="methodTitle">
            <h2>ü•ó Sides + Timing Plan</h2>
            <span class="tag"><span class="dot"></span> complete dinner flow</span>
          </div>
          <div class="hint">15‚Äì25 min</div>
        </div>

        <div class="cardBody">
          <div class="twoCol">
            <div class="box">
              <h3>Fast sides (choose one)</h3>
              <ul>
                <li><b>Roasted potatoes:</b> 425¬∞F for 20‚Äì30 min (start first).</li>
                <li><b>Rice:</b> set it and forget it (start first).</li>
                <li><b>Salad:</b> while trout cooks.</li>
                <li><b>Veg:</b> asparagus or green beans, quick saut√©.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="box">
              <h3>15‚Äì25 minute plan</h3>
              <div class="steps">
                <div class="step"><p>Start rice/potatoes if using (they take longest).</p></div>
                <div class="step"><p>Prep trout: rinse ‚Üí pat dry ‚Üí season ‚Üí apply flavor path.</p></div>
                <div class="step"><p>Heat your oven/grill/pan and start trout timer.</p></div>
                <div class="step"><p>Make salad / veg while trout cooks.</p></div>
                <div class="step"><p>Check thickest part, rest 3 minutes, plate like you meant it.</p></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="story fine" style="margin-top:10px">
            The real secret is pacing: sides first, fish last, and you look like a wizard.
          </p>
        </div>
